data.title: Alan Arkin, actor known for "Little Miss Sunshine" and "Edward Scissorhands," dies at 89
data.meta_description: Renowned actor Alan Arkin, who won an Academy Award for his performance in "Little Miss Sunshine," has died at the age of 89. Janet Shamlian takes a look back at his life.
